<HEADLINE> Kuwait Has Trade Surplus in First Three Quarters </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait earned a trade surplus
of 1.4 billion Kuwaiti dinars (4.62 billion U.S. dollars) in the
first three quarters of 1997, according to official statistics
released on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kuwait exported 3.22 billion dinars (10.63 billion dollars)
worth of goods, of which 3.16 billion dinars (10.43 billion
dollars) were oil revenues, in the period, the Kuwaiti Central
Statistics Department of the Planning Ministry said in a
newsletter.
</P>
<P>
The statistics showed that Kuwait's imports, meanwhile, reached
1.82 billion dinars (6.01 billion dollars).
</P>
<P>
Japan was the biggest exporter to Kuwait in the period, with a
proportion of 17.2 percent of its market, according to the figures.
</P>
<P>
The United States and Germany followed Japan with respective
proportions of 11.7 percent and 7.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The newsletter said Kuwait mainly bought 168.7 dinars (556.71
million dollars) worth of cars, 42.5 million dinars (140.25
million dollars) of auto spare parts, and 81.9 million dinars
(270.27 million dollars) of power generators and water equipment.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Kuwait's volume of imports from Gulf Arab states
stood at 192.8 million dinars (636.24 million dollars) and exports
at 65.3 million dinars (215.49 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
Gulf Arab states are Saudi Arabia, Qatar, Bahrain, Oman and the
United Arab Emirates. 
</P>
</TEXT>
