<HEADLINE> BJP Leader Vajpayee Appointed as New Prime Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- President K. R. Narayanan
Sunday night appointed Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) senior leader
A. B. Vajpayee as new prime minister of the next government after
talks with him on the government formation.
</P>
<P>
The letter of appointment was given to Vajpayee when he called
on the president here Sunday evening.
</P>
<P>
The president invited Vajpayee shortly after newly appointed
Congress President Sonia Gandhi conveyed to the president that her
party did not have the requisite numbers of MPs to form a
government on its own though informal consultations were on with
like-minded parties.
</P>
<P>
The United Front, the third biggest formation, decided Sunday
to sit in the opposition in Parliament following its debacle in
the general elections.
</P>
<P>
The swearing-in ceremony will take place on March 19, Vajpayee
told newsmen after his meeting with the President. 
</P>
</TEXT>
