<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 18:10 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 5 Killed, 50 Injured in Iran's Earthquake </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A strong earthquake on Saturday
has killed five people and injured 50 in Iran's southeastern
province of Kerman, a relief official said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA quoted Red Crescent Society
official Mohammad Dabaghzadeh as saying that the quake inflicted
heavy damage on about 2,000 residential units of 3,600 houses in
the district of Golbaf, some 950 kilometers south of Tehran.
</P>
<P>
The quake, measuring 6.8 degrees on the open-ended Richter
scale, occurred at 23:12 local time (1942 GMT) in Golbaf district,
well-known for hand-woven carpets, and affected some 15
surrounding villages.
</P>
<P>
Golbaf has a population of 24,000. In 1981, an earthquake of
the same magnitude rocked the region, killing 1,000 people.
</P>
<P>
IRNA attributed the low casualties in Saturday's quake to the
safety measures taken in construction of buildings in the wake of
the 1981 quake.
</P>
<P>
Head of the provincial headquarters for natural disasters
Mohsen Salehi said the relief operations to rescue those trapped
under the debris were completed within four hours after the quake.
</P>
<P>
He said the hit areas were quickly identified and relief
workers rushed to the area 20 minutes after the quake. A total of
23 ambulances, 2,550 blankets, 370 makeshift tents, food and
medicines were immediately dispatched to the region, he added.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, IRNA reported that the central and southwestern
provinces of Kohkilouyeh, Boyer Ahmad and Yazd were also jolted by
mild quakes over the past two days. No reports were available
about possible casualties. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
