<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-15 18:13 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Egypt Awards Giant Project to Public Bidders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A contract was signed here Sunday
to build one of the world's largest pumping stations for a huge
land reclamation project in Egypt by a group of Egyptian and
foreign companies, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Described as a "unique engineering project," the station will
pump water from Egypt's largest man-made lake, Lake Nasser, into
the Sheikh Zayed Canal, which is now under construction for a year.
</P>
<P>
The pumping station will be built in four years at a total cost
of 1.48 billion Egyptian pounds (435.3 million U.S. dollars) by
Egyptian, British, Japanese and Norwegian companies.
</P>
<P>
The Egyptian component will be about 25 percent of the total
cost of mechanical works and about 50 percent for civil works.
</P>
<P>
The canal, known as the South Valley or Toshka project, is
designed to pump 5 billion cubic meters of water a year from Lake
Nasser into the Western Desert to bring one million feddans
(420,000 hectares) under cultivation.
</P>
<P>
The investments of the South Valley project amount to about 300
billion pounds (88.2 billion dollars), and the government will
bear 20 percent, in cash, for the infrastructure, said Prime
Minister Kamal el-Ganzouri, who attended the signing ceremony with
other cabinet members.
</P>
<P>
The contract was signed by engineer Abdel Latif Askar, head of
the Mechanical Department at the Ministry of Public Works and
Water Resources, and a representative of the Union of the Egyptian
and Foreign Companies which will carry out the project.
</P>
<P>
Mahmoud Abu Zeid, minister of public works and water resources,
said that the station includes a 4.5 kilometer inlet inside Lake
Nasser to adjust to water level changes, a sucking basin and a
discharge basin, administrative buildings, workshops and annexed
laboratories.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Electricity is building a transformers station
now to feed the pumping station. It will be ready in 15 months.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
