<HEADLINE> Iran Raps U.S. Double Standard over Nuclear Issue </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran on Sunday blamed the United
States for its double-standard stance towards nuclear projects in
different countries, and repeated its call for freeing the Middle
East from weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said the U.S. is launching a
"unsubstantiated propaganda" against Iran to divert attention from
the U.S. support for Israel and its stockpile of nuclear weaponry.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. propaganda, Mohammadi said, "seeks to deprive
independent countries of economic and industrial development."
</P>
<P>
He stressed that Iran's nuclear activities were for peaceful
objectives, and its cooperation with other countries in the field
of nuclear technology fully complies with international
regulations.
</P>
<P>
Besides, he said the International Atomic Energy Agency is
monitoring Iran's nuclear facilities.
</P>
<P>
He criticized the U.S. double-standard stance towards the
issue of nuclear capability by various states, voicing Tehran's
position that the Middle East region should be free from weapons
of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
"The regional countries should pay due attention to the serious
threat posed by the Zionist regime (Israel) and should further
move through international organizations to control the regime's
weapons of mass destruction," the spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
Iran puts emphasis on eradication of weapons of mass
destruction, and within the framework of the Organization of the
Islamic Conference, it would pursue its goal of ridding the region
of such weapons, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
