<HEADLINE> E. African Women Suffer Most From Unsafe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Thirty out of 1,000 women
in east African countries, including Tanzania, died from unsafe
abortions in 1996, according to a recent report from the World
Health Organization.
</P>
<P>
The report which was made available on Sunday said that east
African countries take the lead in the world in the rate of
deaths caused by unsafe abortions.
</P>
<P>
Most of the women died of unsafe abortions were between 15 and
49 years of age, it said.
</P>
<P>
Other countries with high mortality rate from unsafe abortions
are in Latin America and west Africa.
</P>
<P>
Countries with the lowest rates of deaths from abortions
are Australia, far-east countries and the United States, where
four out of 1,000 women died from abortions in 1996.  
</P>
</TEXT>
