<HEADLINE> Israel's General Killed in Chopper Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- An Israeli Air Force brigadier
general and his crewman were killed Sunday morning when their
Cobra attack helicopter crashed into the Mediterranean Sea, Israel
TV channel 1 said.
</P>
<P>
Brig. Gen. Tal Shmuel Eldar, 45, and 20-year-old second
lieutenant Ilan Gur, were killed in the chopper crash. Eldar was
the highest-ranking Israel Air Force officer ever killed in an
military air accident.
</P>
<P>
The crash occurred about 24 kilometers north of Tel Aviv, off
Kibbutz Gash and the chopper was headed for Palmachim air force
base, about 16 kilomters south of Tel Aviv, where Eldar was
commander, the TV added.
</P>
<P>
Israeli navy boats and helicopters combed the area following
the crash, but the bodies had not been recovered.
</P>
<P>
The army has opened an investigation of the crash and grounded
its Cobra fleet. 
