<HEADLINE> ECOWAS to Establish Regional Peace, Security </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Ministers of the 16-member
Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS) have endorsed
the establishment of a sub-regional peace and security
observation system as part of their efforts to contain and defuse
conflicts in the region.
</P>
<P>
The system would monitor, analyze and address breakdowns in
relations between member states, the News Agency of Nigeria
reported Sunday, quoting a communique at the end of a meeting in
Yamoussoukro, Cote d'Ivoir over the weekend.
</P>
<P>
The two-day meeting was attended by ECOWAS ministers of
foreign affairs, defense, internal affairs and state security.
</P>
<P>
The system would also assist in resolving breakdowns in social
and political situations within member states.
</P>
<P>
The ministers therefore directed experts and the ECOWAS
secretariat to work out a mechanism for the realization of this
purpose, using the sub-regional peacekeeping force ECOMOG as the
framework.
</P>
<P>
The mechanism will incorporate the composition of troops,
decision-making process, relations between troops and political
authorities, deployment, political and diplomatic management of
crisis, command structure, training and finance, among others.
</P>
</TEXT>
