<HEADLINE> Syria Denounces Israeli Obstructing Peace Process </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Syria on Sunday denounced Israel
for its hardline policy which has obstructed the progress of the
Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The peace process is on the brink of collapse due to Israel's
racist and anti-peace policies, Syrian Vice President Zuhair
Masharqa said at a ceremony marking the Arab Teachers' Day.
</P>
<P>
Israel is endeavoring to displace the inhabitants and owners of
the occupied Arab territories, exercising racism, oppression and
terrorism, he said.
</P>
<P>
Recent massacre in Hebron stands as an evidence of that policy,
he added, referring to three Palestinian workers killed by Israeli
troops last Tuesday at a roadblock near the West Bank city when
they drove back to Palestinian self-rule areas.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian leader reaffirmed that peace is the strategic option
of Arab countries.
</P>
<P>
Syria is seeking a just and comprehensive peace that will
provide security for all nations in the region, based on Israeli
pullback from all occupied Arab territories to the June 4, 1967
borders, from south Lebanon and the West Bekaa, he stressed.
</P>
<P>
Likewise, the legitimate rights of the Palestinian people
should be ensured, which include their right to returning home,
self-determination and an independent statehood on their national
soil.
</P>
<P>
Masharqa accused Israel's construction and expansion of Jewish
settlements, judaization of Jerusalem and execution of racist
repression and brutal terrorism against the Arabs on the occupied
territories. 
</P>
</TEXT>
