<HEADLINE> Pakistan, Oman to Cooperate in Environment Field </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Oman agreed on
Monday to cooperate in the field of environment, including
protecting threatened wild life species, controlling marine
pollution and hazardous waste management.
</P>
<P>
This was decided at a meeting held here between Pakistani
Minister of State for Environment Syed Ahmad Mahmud and visiting
Oman's Minister for Environment Khamis Bin Mubarak, according to
the Associated Press of Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
During the meeting, Ahmad Mahmud said despite resource
constraints Pakistan had been taking practical steps to protect
the environment in collaboration with various agencies.
</P>
<P>
He stressed the need to exchange information and expertise
between Pakistan and Oman.
</P>
<P>
Mubarak said that environment programs in his country were
introduced as early as 27 years ago.
</P>
<P>
The two ministers expressed the hope that the two countries
will learn from each other's experience and cooperate in the field
of environment for the benefit of future generations. 
</P>
