<HEADLINE> Sonia Gandhi elected Chairperson of India's CPP </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Sonia Gandhi, new president of
India's Congress party, was unanimously elected chairperson of the
Congress Parliamentary Party (CPP) on Monday, the Press Trust of
India (PTI) reported.
</P>
<P>
Sonia Gandhi, Congress star campaigner in the just-concluded
general elections to the 12th Lower House of the Parliament, was
elected at a general body meeting of the CPP in late afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The meeting ratified a decision taken earlier Monday by the CPP
Executive Committee to amend the CPP's constitution to enable the
newly-elected Congress leader to become chairperson of the CPP.
</P>
<P>
Sonia Gandhi, whose Italian origin gave her opponents
propaganda grist, succeeded Sitaram Kesri to become the new
president of the Congress party Saturday at a meeting of the
Congress Working Committee, the highest decision-making body of
the party.
</P>
<P>
The dual chief of the century-old Congress is neither a member
of Lok Sabha, the House of the People, nor a member of Rajya
Sabha, the Council of States.
</P>
<P>
In 1978, when Indira Gandhi, Sonia Gandhi's mother-in-law, was
made chairperson of the CPP, she was also not a member of either
house.
</P>
<P>
The 52-year-old widow of assassinated former prime minister
Rajiv Gandhi was born into a family of modest means in an obscure
village on the banks of river Po Neat Turin northwest of Italy.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
