<HEADLINE> Hong Kong SAR Athletes, Associations Awarded </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Amateur Sports Federation
and Olympic Committee of Hong Kong, China, presented here on
Monday a record sum of incentive awards to outstanding athletes
and associations of the Special Administrative Region (SAR) for
their performances at major international competitions last year
and earlier this year.
</P>
<P>
Commemorative plaques were also presented to Cheung Wai Leung
of the local association for the physically disabled, Carl C. Kwok
of the yachting association, Wushu master Ng Siu Ching, soccer
player Yu Kam Kee and wind surfer Lee Lai Shan.
