<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Jobless Rate Up </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in Hong
Kong rose to 2.9 percent for the three months ending in February
while the underemployment rate edged up to 1.6 percent, the
government said in the labor force figures released here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The jobless rate for the period between November 1997 and
January 1998 was 2.5 percent while the underemployment rate was
1.5 percent, according to the Census and Statistics Department.
</P>
<P>
A government spokesman said Monday that the distinct rise in
the unemployment rate was observed after the Chinese New Year
holidays, which fell on the last few days in January. He said
employers usually adjusted their work force during this period of
the year.
</P>
<P>
The Asian financial turmoil and the consequential setback in
the local economy also produced a negative effect on the labor
market, said the spokesman.
</P>
<P>
The increase in the unemployment rate was mostly found in such
sectors as construction, retail trade, restaurants and hotels,
real estate and manufacturing.
</P>
<P>
The spokesman said the government's substantial expenditure
program on public housing and new infrastructure projects would
continue to provide job opportunities at a time when the current
economic setback led to slackening job creation in the private
sector.
</P>
<P>
He noted that the extensive tax concessions proposed in the
1998-99 financial budget would help boost consumption and create
employment opportunities in retail sectors.  
</P>
</TEXT>
