<HEADLINE> First Session of Ninth CPPCC Standing Committee Closes In Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The two-day first session of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth Chinese People's Political
Consultative Conference (CPPCC) National Committee ended here
today.
</P>
<P>
Li Ruihuan, chairman of the National Committee of the CPPCC,
delivered a speech at the session today, which arranged the
establishment of all its subcommittees and appointed 16 deputy
secretary generals of the CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Li, also a Standing Committee member of the Political Bureau of
the Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC), said
that the Ninth CPPCC National Committee should adapt to the
country's new situation, drawing new experience, developing itself
while adhering to the proper principles and practices of the
Eighth CPPCC National Committee.
</P>
<P>
"The Standing Committee members of the CPPCC National Committee
should be united tightly, implementing the principle of democratic
political consultation, and discussing national affairs on a equal
basis," he said, adding that the members should learn from each
other and support each other to create an amicable atmosphere in
the organization.
</P>
<P>
Nine subcommittees were set up in the session, with each of the
committee heads appointed. The subcommittee of human resources and
the environment was set up for the first time by the CPPCC
National Committee.
</P>
<P>
Ye Xuanping, vice-chairman of the CPPCC National Committee
presided over today's session. 
</P>
</TEXT>
