<HEADLINE> Olympic Champion Wang Junxia Still Training: Official </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Olympic champion and world record
holder Wang Junxia has fully recovered from injury and resumed
normal training in her home province Liaoning, an sports official
said here on Monday.
</P>
<P>
"She is training under a normal schedule," said Cui Dalin, head
of the Liaoning Physicial Culture and Sports Commission.
</P>
<P>
Wang, who won China's only Olympic track and field gold in the
women's 5,000 meters event in the 1996 Games, had not returned to
the track until late last year following her Atlanta triumph.
</P>
<P>
Cui said Wang has been coached by Wang Helin after her coach
Mao Dezhen retired late last year.
</P>
<P>
Mao took charge of Wang after the 10,000m world record holder
broke away from legendary coach Ma Junren's training camp in 1994.
</P>
<P>
Liu Dong, who won the women's 800m gold in Stuggart and split
with Ma together with Wang, was also under the coach of Wang
Helin, Cui said.
</P>
<P>
Cui also said that coach Ma was working hard in establishing
the Liaoning track and field training base. "His health was
really worrying," Cui said, adding Ma still had blood in his
stool.
</P>
<P>
Ma led his new team to win the Beijing women's marathon
relay race on February 28. The new protegees, including Jiang Bo,
Dong Yanmei, Zhao Fengting, Ma Zaijie, Lan Lixin, and Lin Na, set
a race record of two hours 11 minutes and 35 seconds over 42.195
kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Bo also broke the women's 5,000 world record in the
Chinese Eighth National Games last October in Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
"Their performance last month boosted our confidence," said
Cui. "If they continued to work hard, the Sydney Olympic Games
will be the right place for them to emerge as glittering stars."
</P>
</TEXT>
