<HEADLINE> Mongolian President Arrives in Turkey for Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Mongolian President Nachagyn
Bagabandy arrived at the Ankara Esenboga Airport Monday morning
for a two-day state visit to Turkey, the first of its kind by a
Mongolian president.
</P>
<P>
Bagabandy is paying a return visit to Turkey following Turkish
President Suleyman Demirel's trip to Mongolia in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Mongolian president is heading a large delegation
including high-ranking government and parliamentary officials.
</P>
<P>
Turkey and Mongolia are expected to sign an agreement
concerning the reciprocal encouragement and protection of
investments and a convention in the field of veterinary medicine
during Bagabandy's visit.
</P>
<P>
Turkey's Daily News Monday quoted Mongolian Ambassador to
Ankara Altangerel Bulgaa as saying that Mongolian officials
believe that their country can find a venue for exporting copper,
enriched copper and other minerals to Turkey. 
</P>
