<HEADLINE> Philippines' Garment, Textile Exports Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Philippines' garment and
textile exports for the first two months of the year reached
nearly 460 million U.S. dollars, down by 3 percent from the same
period last year, official figures showed Monday.
</P>
<P>
Data released Monday by the country's Garments and Textile
Export Board traced the slight decline to the drop in European and
non-quota countries' purchases during the period.
</P>
<P>
The country's garment and textile exports to quota and
non-quota nations decreased by 13 and 23 percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
Among the non-quota countries, Japan was the biggest buyer of
the Philippines' garments and textiles with a payment of 27.7
million dollars during the period.
</P>
<P>
The United States remained the biggest market among the quota
countries with purchases amounting to 304 million dollars.
</P>
</TEXT>
