<HEADLINE> Baig Calls for Greater Pakistani-Iranian Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistan and Iran should
cooperate with each other and develop an all-time friendship to
counter the odds, Pakistan's former army chief General (R) Aslam
Baig said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Addressing a seminar on "Globalization: Prospects for Economic
Development in Iran and Pakistan", Baig said Iran and Pakistan had
long friendship and in today's changed international environment
the two countries should join hands for enhanced cooperation.
</P>
<P>
On the occasion, Iranian Ambassador to Pakistan Mehdi
Akhundzada criticized the U.S. for its policy of sanctions and
embargoes. He also defended Iran's policy on global information
technology. Cultural heritage must be defended against the inflow
of satellite programs, he said.
</P>
<P>
