<HEADLINE> Progress in HK's Toilet Improvement Scheme </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 352 toilets in Hong
Kong have been improved, accounting for nearly a half of 678
toilets which are included in the Toilet Improvement Scheme.
</P>
<P>
The remaining toilets are either in progress or under
feasibility study, the provisional Regional Council said here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Toilet Improvement Scheme being carried out by the
Provisional Regional Council is designed to provide better public
toilet facilities and improve environment in Hong Kong.
</P>
<P>
Toilet improvement works include refurbishment of internal and
external fittings, changes of trough type toilets to squat or
pedestal type water closets, and conversion of aqua privies to
flushed toilets if possible.
</P>
<P>
There are now 604 aqua privies (dry toilets) and 133 flushed
toilets managed by the relevant environment health
departments. 
</P>
</TEXT>
