<HEADLINE> China Releases Jan-Feb Primary and Industrial Trade Figures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) --China's exports of industrial
products grew by 20 percent to 22.08 billion US dollars for the
first two months this year and accounted for 88.9 percent of the
total export volume, according to statistics released by the
General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
Exports of machinery and electronic products grew by 33.2
percent to 8.75 billion US dollars, with a further breakdown
showing that exports of machinery and logistical equipment jumped
by 38.2 percent to 6.67 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
China exported primary products valued at 2.76 billion US
dollars, down 10.1 percent on the 1996 period, with related
products accounting for 11.1 percent of total exports.
</P>
<P>
Imports of primary goods fell by 21.4 percent to 3.19 billion
US dollars, with the figure for industrial products growing by 6.2
percent to 14.5 billion dollars. The latter figure included 7.71
billion US dollars in imports of machinery and electronic goods,
up 7.2 percent on the previous year's figure. 
</P>
</TEXT>
