<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China's general trade exports for
the first two months of 1998 grew by 9.3 percent to 10.22 billion
US dollars, or 41.2 percent of the total export volume, according
to statistics released by China's General Administration of
Customs.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, general trade imports for the period slumped
by 11.9 percent to end at 4.36 billion US dollars.
</P>
