<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> S'pore Steps Up Efforts to Promote Chinese Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Singapore is stepping up its
efforts to promote Chinese Internet as the government announced on
Monday that it has set up a Steering Committee to establish
Singapore as a cyber hub for Chinese Internet.
</P>
<P>
Announcing the setting up of the Committee, George Yeo,
Minister for Information and the Arts, said at the Parliament
session that many Singaporeans are fluent in the language and
China is expected to have up to 4 million Internet users by the
year of 2000.
</P>
<P>
This was the time to make headway in this area, the Minister
said, adding that the members of the committee come from a cross
section of organizations.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information and the Arts (MITA) said in a
statement that the Committee was set up to look into ways to
promote the development and the use of Chinese Internet among
Singaporeans.
</P>
<P>
The Committee is chaired by Professor Wee Chow Hou, Dean of the
Business Administration, National University of Singapore. Prof.
Wee is also the Chairman of the Committee to Promote the Use of
Mandarin.
</P>
<P>
As its tasks, the Committee will promote the awareness and use
of Chinese Internet, and seek community support and industry
collaboration for the promotion of Chinese Internet, the Ministry
said.
</P>
<P>
It will also recommend policy directions, and oversee the
development of Chinese Internet in Singapore. In addition, the
Committee will help establish Singapore as the focal point for the
development of technologies which bridge Chinese and English
Internet environments, with participation from both local and
foreign organizations, the Ministry said.
</P>
<P>
It added that the Committee held its inaugural meeting on
February 11. And it is working out a plan of action, which aims to
coordinate efforts from various sectors into an overall strategy
to promote Singapore as a cyber hub for Chinese Internet. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0097 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
