<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0099 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Maintains Growth in Export for First Two Months of 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China's exports grew by 15.7
percent to 24.83 billion US dollars for the first two months of
this year, compared with the same 1997 period, according to
statistics released by the General Administration of Customs.
</P>
<P>
The total Jan-Feb trade volume jumped by 8.5 percent to 42.52
billion US dollars, with imports of 17.69 billion US dollar
remaining basically at last year's period level.
</P>
<P>
China trade surplus for the first two months of the year stood
at 7.14 billion dollars.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded processing enterprises exported products valued
at 9.21 billion US dollars and accounted for 52 percent of the net
growths. The former figure represented growth of 23.1 percent, or
1.73 billion US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Solely foreign-funded processing enterprises witnessed the most
rapid growth, with exports rising by 30.4 percent to 4.04 billion
US dollars.
</P>
<P>
Total period exports for China's processing industry grew by
18.7 percent to 13.83 billion US dollars, and accounted for 55.7
percent of the nation's total exports.
</P>
<P>
Foreign-funded enterprises as a whole exported products valued
at 10.59 billion dollars and accounted for 42.7 percent of total
exports, up 22 percent on the 1996 period. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
