<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Lower </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange (KLSE) closed broadly lower Monday in thin
trading as players stayed on the sideline on uncertainty of market
directions.
</P>
<P>
The market turned weak in the afternoon after firming slightly
in the morning on lack of fresh leads.
</P>
<P>
The 100-companies benchmark Composite Index lost 4.55 points to
703.61, the all Main Board Emas Index 1.27 points to 178.09 and
the Industrial Index 6.03 points to 1,269.74, while the Second
Board Index dropped 0.3 points to 179.65.
</P>
<P>
Losers outnumbered gainers by 416 to 228 while 135 counters
were unchanged and 151 untraded.
</P>
<P>
Monday's turnover stood at 121.462 million shares valued at
307.765 million ringgit (80.99 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Turnover on the Main Board dropped to 108.56 million shares
valued at 277.208 million ringgit (72.949 million dollars) from
last Friday's 147.608 million shares valued at 362.2 million
ringgit (95.316 million dollars).
</P>
<P>
On the Second Board, volume shrank to 12.902 million valued at
30.557 million ringgit (8.041 million dollars) from 19.785 million
valued at 45.366 million ringgit (11.938 million dollars) last
Friday.
</P>
<P>
But direct business deals soared to 34.896 million shares
valued at 69.632 million ringgit (18.324 million dollars) from
3.862 million shares valued at 25.139 million ringgit (6.615
million dollars) last Friday.
</P>
<P>
On a sectoral basis, consumer products accounted for 6.03
million shares traded on the main board, industrial products
11.039 million shares, construction 12.416 million shares,
trade/service 26.712 million shares, infrastructure 516,000
shares, finance 16.359 million shares, hotels 521,000 shares,
properties 8.372 million shares, plantations 7.528 million shares,
mining 645,000 shares, trusts 62,000 shares, closed-end fund
62,000 shares and loans 18.299 million shares.  
</P>
</TEXT>
