<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading French Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news items in
leading French newspapers Monday:
</P>
<P>
Liberation:
</P>
<P>
-- The ruling leftwing coalition of France came ahead of the
rightwing opposition in the regional elections held on Sunday
without being able to obtain the scores they won in the legislative
elections last year. Aggravating the crisis within the rightwing
opposition, the leftwing coalition could obtain majority in at least
eight regional councils or parliaments, including that of Paris and
Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur, while the extreme-left will also enter
some regional councils.
</P>
<P>
-- The chief of the team of the opposition RPR and UDF in Paris,
Edouard Balladur, has called for the forming of an organization
rallying ``all the republican and liberal right'', after he lost the
campaign for the Paris council. The far right National Front (FN)
again won 15 percent of votes and increased their capacity in local
parliaments. Both the RPR and UDF have ruled out an alliance with
FN.
</P>
<P>
Le Figaro:
</P>
<P>
-- The regional elections on Sunday confirmed the electoral
supremacy of the leftwing parties, established less than a year ago
during the legislative elections. Interior Minister Jean-Pierre
Chevenement announced that the rightwing oppositions were ``beaten
in 13 of the 20 regions they had controlled in France proper.'' The
right lost mainly the regional councils or parliaments of the Paris
region, Provence-Alpes-Cote d'Azur and Midi-Pyrenees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
