<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher in Sluggish Trade </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks closed here
Monday with the Hang Seng Index rising 124.51 points, or 1.12
percent, to 11,181.54.
</P>
<P>
The value of turnover remained thin at 5.011 billion HK dollars
(642 million U.S. dollars), 224 million HK dollars (28.7 million
U.S. dollars) less than that of last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Finance stocks led the way, advancing 207.43 points or 1.32
percent, followed by three other sub-sectors -- utilities,
commerce and properties -- all of which recorded modest gains.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Hang Seng Index opened 22.57 points, or 0.2
percent, lower at 11,034.46 Monday morning. The stocks finished
its morning session with the Hang Seng Index climbing 97.54
points, or 0.88 percent, to 11,154.57.
</P>
<P>
The Hang Seng Index rose 154.56 points, or 1.42 percent, to
close at 11,057.03 last Friday.
</P>
<P>
Trade was thin throughout the week with average daily turnover
of 5.5 billion HK dollars (705 million U.S. dollars) against the
average 9.34 billion HK dollars (1.197 billion U.S. dollars) for
the year.  
</P>
