<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 10:36 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 55 PKK Rebels Killed in Turkey's Military </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Turkish security forces ended the
four-day-long military operations agianst the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) in Sirnak province bordering northern Iraq,
killing 55 PKK rebels, an official statement said Monday.
</P>
<P>
The statement issued by the office of Emergency Regional Rule
said that the Turkish security forces started the large-scale
military operations by bombing the PKK camps in Besteler and
Dereler regions of southeastern province of Sirnak on March 12
and ended the military operations on Monday morning.
</P>
<P>
Twenty-three PKK rebels were killed during the first two-day
clashes between the goveernment troops and the PKK guerrillas in
the region, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
It said that 24 PKK militants were shot dead in the armed
clashes in the same regions on Saturday evening and Sunday
morning.
</P>
<P>
Eight PKK guerrillas were killed during the four-day-long
military operations in Sirnak, said the statement.
</P>
<P>
However, it said that three soldiers of the security forces
were also killed in the conflicts over the past four days.
</P>
<P>
Some 2,500 or 3,000 PKK militants, who have sheltered
themselves in northern Iraq since the 1991 Gulf War, often cross
into Turkey from northern Iraq and attack military and civilian
targets in the country.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting a 13-year-old separatist war for
autonomy in eastern and southeastern Turkey, which has claimed
over 28,000 lives since August 1984. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
