<HEADLINE> Congress to Amend Constitution </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Executive Committee of
India's Congress Parliamentary Party (CPP) decided Monday to amend
its constitution, a Congress spokesman said here.
</P>
<P>
Emerging from a 30-minute emergency meeting of the executive
body, Ajit Jogi said the amendment is to enable newly-elected
Congress leader Sonia Gandhi to become chairperson of the CPP.
</P>
<P>
The decision would be placed for approval at a general body
meeting of the CPP scheduled for Monday evening, Jogi said.
</P>
<P>
Gandhi, Congress star campaigner in the just-concluded general
elections to the 12th lower house of the parliament, Lok Sabha,
succeeded Sitaram Kesri to become the new president of the
Congress party last Saturday.
</P>
<P>
She is neither a member of Lok Sabha, the House of the People,
nor a member of Rajya Sabha, the Council of States.
</P>
<P>
In 1978, when Indira Gandhi, her mother-in-law, was made
chairperson of the CPP, she was also not a member of either house
and many party leaders favor a revival of the post.  
</P>
</TEXT>
