<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Records Rise in Actual Funding Rate for Key Projects </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China invested a total of 147.5
billion yuan (17.8 billion US dollars) in 129 key national
construction projects in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The figure represented 96.7 percent of the budgeted figure, or
a rate some 0.8 percentage points higher than in 1996, according
to a report of the China Economic Herald.
</P>
<P>
A further breakdown shows that the central government
contributed 124.1 billion yuan of the total investments, with
local governments providing the remaining 23.4 billion yuan. The
invetments of the central government and the local governments
accounted for 98.2 percent and 89.1 percent of their planned
investments, respectively.
</P>
<P>
The total volume of delayed investments in key national
construction projects has continued to decline in recent years,
with the 1997 figure falling by 1.8 billion yuan on 1996,
according to the newspaper. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
