<HEADLINE> Moscow's Anti-Criminal Combat Fruitful </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The Moscow Regional Department for
Combating Organized Crimes (RDCOC) handled 9,871 criminal cases
over the past five years, the Itar-Tass news agency reported
Monday.
</P>
<P>
The agency quoted police chief Nikolai Klimkin as saying that
RDCOC crashed 2,827 organized bandit gangs, and seized 4,000
pieces of firearms, 1,053 kilograms of explosives and 571
kilograms of drugs.
</P>
<P>
During this period, RDCOC arrested 56 ringleaders and 246
smaller gang leaders.
</P>
<P>
RDCOC received 952 reports about kidnappings in the last five
years. 51 of the hostages were children and were all saved, he
added. In addition, more than 1,000 people involved in these
kidnapings were arrested. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
