<HEADLINE> Four-Party Talks on Korean Peninsula Begin in Geneva </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENEVA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The second plenary session of the
four-party talks to seek a lasting and stable peace on the Korean
Peninsula began here in Geneva on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Chen Jian, deputy foreign minister of China, chairs the talks
expected to last five days.
</P>
<P>
According to agreement reached at the first round which was
held in Geneva last December, the four-party talks will be held in
an interval of every three months for years, and the chair will
rotate among the four, the United States, China, South Korea and
the Democratic People's Republic of Korea (DPRK).
</P>
<P>
The four parties are trying to reach consensus on a peace
treaty to replace an armistice signed in 1953 when the fighting on
the Korean Peninsula ended.
</P>
<P>
Switzerland is the host country of the talks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
