<HEADLINE> Xu Jialu, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Xu Jialu, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC).
</P>
<P>
Xu, male, of Han Nationality, born in June 1937, native of
Huai'an, Jiangsu Province, member of China Association for
Promoting Democracy (CAPD), graduated from Department of
Chinese Language of Beijing Teachers University in 1959.
</P>
<P>
Served as lecturer, associate professor, professor, deputy
department dean, department dean and director of teaching research
office of Chinese Language Department of Beijing Normal
University, 1959-87; vice-president of Beijing Teachers
University, vice-chairman of Beijing Municipal Committee of
People's Political Consultative Conference, and Standing Committee
member and vice-chairman of CAPD Central Committee, 1987-94;
director of State Language Work Committee, 1994-97; chairman of
CAPD Central Committee since 1997 and director of the State
Language Work Committee.
</P>
<P>
He was elected a deputy to Seventh and Eighth National People's
Congress (NPC), member of NPC Standing Committee, and member of
the NPC Education, Science, Culture and Public Health Committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
