<HEADLINE> Jiang Zhenghua, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Jiang Zhenghua, who was just elected vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress
(NPC):
</P>
<P>
Jiang, male, of Han nationality, born in October 1937, native
of Hangzhou, Zhejiang Province, member of Committee of Chinese
Peasants and Workers Democratic Party (CPWDP).
</P>
<P>
Graduated from Electrical Machinery Department of Xi'an
Jiaotong University, 1958; served as lecturer and deputy director
of Systematic Engineering Research Institute, 1958-80; studied as
graduate student at Bombay International Demography Academy,
India, 1980-1982; director of Population and Economics Institute of
Xi'an Jiaotong University, professor, 1982-1991; vice-chairman of
State Family Planning Commission and vice-chairman of CPWDP
Central Committee, 1991-97; chairman of CPWDP Central Committee
since 1997.
</P>
<P>
He was member of Seventh National Committee of Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC) and member of
Standing Committee of Eighth CPPCC National Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
