<HEADLINE> Foreign Investment Increases in Uganda </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Foreign investment in the
country increased from 851 million U.S. Dollars in 1996 to 1.566
billion U.S. Dollars in Uganda, the New Vision reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
But individual investors complained about the incomplete
services in transport, land accessibility and capacity
utilization, though they conceded there are some improvement in
the service delivery.
</P>
<P>
Both foreign investments and joint ventures are in increasing
trend, said Uganda investment authority in its year activity
report in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The report said increased foreign investments translate into
greater capital, technology and skills transfer.
</P>
<P>
The increasing number of joint venture partnership enables
local investors to select foreign investor and technology and in
turn enable the foreign investors to link with reliable local
partners who are more familiar with the local environment.
</P>
</TEXT>
