<HEADLINE> Northeast China's Liaoning to Sell Off More SOEs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Northeast China's Liaoning
Province will prepare more than 500 small and medium-sized
state-owned enterprises (SOE) for sale at a local fair this week.
</P>
<P>
Today's "China Daily" reported that some 14 cities will attend
the fair which will be held in Shenyang, the provincial capital,
on Saturday and Sunday.
</P>
<P>
"We intend to push completely all the medium-sized and small
SOEs onto the market through the fair," the newspaper quoted an
official of Liaoning Provincial Economic and Trade Commission as
saying.
</P>
<P>
According to the official, the SOEs are selected from a dozen
industries, including petro-chemical, machine-building,
metallurgy, construction materials, textiles, and pharmaceuticals.
</P>
<P>
Liaoning, which is China's oldest industrial base, is home to
one-tenth of China's large SOEs and has 4,000 medium-sized and
small SOEs.
</P>
<P>
The sale of those small SOEs was designed by the province as a
guide to revitalize all SOEs within the next three years, said the
official.  
</P>
</TEXT>
