<HEADLINE> Australian Dollar Closes Softer </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A falling Japanese yen dragged
the Australian dollar off its highs Monday, leaving the local
currency on a weaker note at the local session close in Sydney.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar ended in Sydney at 67.17 US cents from
67.30 late Friday.
</P>
<P>
Paul Macarounas, treasury manager with Rothschild Australia,
said the fortunes of the Australian dollar have been largely tied
to the Japanese yen in recent weeks and Monday was no exception.
</P>
<P>
"Whether that link disappears when the fiscal year ends in
Japan at the end of this month remains to be seen but it is
certainly there now," he said.
</P>
<P>
Early strength in the Japanese yen was reversed following
reports that Finance Minister Hikaru Matsunaga was not considering
an extra budget.
</P>
<P>
The Australian dollar finished at 86.73 yen from 86.35, and at
1.2233 marks from 1.2282 marks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
