<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0151 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hainan Focuses on Industrial Development </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 16 (Xinhua) -- The annual growth rate of
industrial added value in southernmost China's Hainan province
recorded 11.3 percent during 1993-1997.
</P>
<P>
The great achievement is contributed to the effective plan made
by the local goverment, according to the latest statistics. To be
a leading industrial province, the local government has put the
industrial sector in the first place in economic development.
</P>
<P>
During the period, the annual growth rate of the cement,
artificial board, automobiles and cans sectors hit 15.6 percent,
9.9 percent, 20.7 percent and 10.3 percent, respectively.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that before Hainan became a province in April
1988, its industrial output value was less than three billion yuan
and lower than that of the agricultural sector.
</P>
<P>
Thanks to the efforts of rationalizing the structure of
industries, the total industrial output value in the province
surpassed 10 billion yuan in 1994.
</P>
<P>
A group of rising industries have become the province's pillar
ones and the car and motorcycle have emerged as the most
important products in its machine-building industry.
</P>
<P>
According to the statistics, the province has built a polyester
plant with an annual production ability of 60,000 tons,
and a blanket firm which can produce 1.4 million blankets annually.
</P>
<P>
The number of medicine companies has shifted from five in 1978
to the present more than 50. And the beverage products in the
province, especially coconut milk, are famous all over the world.
</P>
<P>
Some industrial development zones have formed and absorbed
great amounts of overseas investment. The Yangpu Economic
Development Zone, for example, has become a base for large
investment projects and China's largest export-bonded zone.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
