<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cheng Siyuan, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Cheng Siyuan, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC):
</P>
<P>
Born in 1908, a native of Binyang, Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous
Region; with no party affiliation; postgraduate from
Rome University, Italy, Ph.D in political science.
</P>
<P>
From 1930 to 1934, worked as political secretary to Li Zongren,
commander-in-chief of Kuomintang (KMT)'s Fourth Group Army, who
was later to become acting president of Republic of China.
</P>
<P>
From 1934, served as secretary to Bai Chongxi, then deputy
chief of staff of KMT National Military Council, chief of Service
Section and director of Central Committee of Three People's
Principles Youth League, director of Political Department of
Guangxi Pacification Headquarters, member of Standing Committee of
KMT Sixth Central Executive Committee, member of KMT Legislative
Committee and deputy secretary general of Wartime Committee of KMT
Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Lived and worked as a columnist for a local newspaper in Hong
Kong, 1949-1965; accompanied Li Zongren to return and settle down
in Beijing in 1965.
</P>
<P>
From 1978-83, was member and deputy secretary general of
Standing Committee of National Committee of Chinese People's
Political Consultative Conference (CPPCC), member of Standing
Committee of National People's Congress (NPC), and vice-chairman
of NPC Foreign Affairs Committee; from 1983-88, member of Standing
Committee and deputy secretary-general of CPPCC National
Committee; after 1993, was vice-chairman of Eighth NPC Standing
Committee. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0153 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Cheng Kejie, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Cheng, male, of Zhuang ethnic group, born in November 1933,
native of Shanglin, Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region, joined
Communist Party of China (CPC) in February 1984, graduated from
Beijing Railway Institute in 1957.
</P>
<P>
Served as railway station intern, technician, engineer, deputy
director and director of Liuzhou Railway Administration, 1957-86;
vice-chairman of Guangxi Zhuang Autonomous Region People's
Government, 1986-89; deputy secretary of CPC Guangxi Zhuang
Autonomous Regional Committee and vice-chairman of the
Autonomous Regional Government, 1989-90; acting chairman and
chairman of the Autonomous Regional People's Government,
1990-Jan.98; and elected member of Central Committee of 14th CPC
Central Committee.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
