<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Russians Snatch Seven Golds at Gymanstic Invitational </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The Russians dominated an
international gymnastic invitational event with a total of seven
golds after teenager Anna Kovalyova produced a spectacular
performance here on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Kovalyova, 15, won the golds in the women's vault, balance beam
and floor exercise, scoring 9.625, 9.600 and 9.575 points
respectively.
</P>
<P>
Her teammate Svetlana Chorkina took the title in the uneven
bars to complete a clean sweep of all four women's golds available
on Sunday, the second day of the Stars of the World competition.
</P>
<P>
In the men's events, Russian Yuri Kryukov, who took the
all-around bronze on Saturday, scored 9.650 points for the pommel
horse title and 9.600 for the vault gold.
</P>
<P>
Another Russian Alexei Bondarenko, the all-round gold medalist
on Saturday, pocketed home the gold from the parallel bars.
</P>
<P>
The men's floor exercise title went to Denmark's Kasper Farden,
Alexander Chostak of Belarus won the rings gold, while German
Karsten Oelsch carried home the horizontal bar gold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
