<HEADLINE> Wang Guangying, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Wang Guangying, who was just elected vice-chairman of
the Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress:
</P>
<P>
Wang, male, of Han nationality, born in Beijing August 1919,
member of China Democratic National Construction Association
(CDNCA), graduated from Fujen Catholic University in 1942.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-chairman and honorary chairman of All-China
Federation of Industry and Commerce, and chairman and general
manager, and honorary chairman of Everbright Group Ltd.
</P>
<P>
Was deputy to First, Second, and Third NPC, vice-chairman of
Eighth NPC Standing Committee, member of Fifth CPPCC National
Committee, and vice-chairman of Sixth and Seventh CPPCC National
Committees.  
</P>
