<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Hunan to Reduce Investments in Capital Construction </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Central China's Hunan Province
will allocate 13.5 billion yuan for 35 major capital construction
projects during 1998.
</P>
<P>
Kang Dingxiong, a senior engineer with the Hunan Key Projects
Office, said fund shortages will force the province to reduce
fixed asset investments involving energy, communications,
telecommunications and water resources.
</P>
<P>
Hunan, located in the middle reaches of the Yangtze River, has
witnessed heavy flooding in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The province will encourage investments in related areas by
reducing levies and taxes of specified projects in order alleviate
financial burden on investors, said Kang.
</P>
<P>
Hunan will ensure investors had easy access to ample supplies
of land, raw materials, equipment, water and power.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
