<HEADLINE> Vietnamese President Arrives for Malaysia Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese President Tran
Duc Luong arrived here Monday afternoon for a three-day state
visit, the first by a Vietnamese head of state to Malaysia since
the two countries established diplomatic ties in 1973.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader's trip, aimed at enhancing bilateral ties
between the two Southeast Asian nations, is to reciprocate the
visit by Malaysian King Tuanku Ja'afar to Vietnam in 1995.
</P>
<P>
The Vietnamese leader is being accompanied by a 35-member
delegation comprising several ministers, deputy ministers, senior
government officials and representatives from the business
community.
</P>
<P>
During the visit, Malaysian Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad
will call on Tran Duc Luong to discuss bilateral relations and the
regional financial crisis, a foreign ministry statement on the
visit said earlier.
</P>
</TEXT>
