<HEADLINE> Vietnamese President Begins Visit to Malaysia, Singapore </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese President Tran Duc Luong
left here Monday for an official visit to Malaysia and Singapore.
</P>
<P>
This is Luong's first overseas trip since being elected
president last September and also the first by a Vietnamese head
of state to the two countries since diplomatic relations were
established 25 years ago, the official daily Nhan Dan said Monday.
</P>
<P>
"The visit will once again reiterate Vietnam's policy of
boosting friendship and accelerating multi-sided cooperation with
neighboring countries," the paper said in an editorial.
</P>
<P>
Malaysia is the seventh largest investor in Vietnam with 60
projects worth more than one billion dollars, the paper said.
</P>
<P>
The two-way trade between the two countries reached 232 million
U.S. dollars in 1997 from 87 million dollars in 1991.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is the largest investor in Vietnam with investments
totaling 6.2 billion dollars as of February.
</P>
<P>
Singapore is also Vietnam's second biggest trade partner with
their annual two-way trade totaling two billion dollars in the
last two years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
