<HEADLINE> French Boat Beats Sailing Mark </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LOS ANGELES, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The French boat Aquitaine
Innovations broke a sailing record from New York to San Francisco
during a competition on Sunday, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Organizers of the Gold Race competition said in San Francisco
that the winning boat, skippered by Frenchman Yves Parlier,
clocked a time of 57 days, three hours to beat the previous mark
of 62 days and five hours.
</P>
<P>
The race, attended by three French boats, was held to recreat
the voyage of some clipper ships carrying supplies to Gold Rush
miners in the 19th century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
