<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Strong Sand Storm Hits Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, March 16 (Xinhua) -- A strong sand storm coming from
the Sahara Desert between Libya and Egypt entered Lebanon Sunday
night from its southern coast and is hitting the country.
</P>
<P>
Sources from Lebanese meteorological department said the
country has seldom seen such a heavy sand storm with the wind
speed of 110 kilometers per hour.
</P>
<P>
The storm, which is also striking other neighboring countries,
especially Cyprus and Egypt, has whipped up low visibility and
affected normal operations in several key airports in the region.
</P>
<P>
Lebanese Voice of the People Radio reported that the Beirut
International Airport and the country's southern port Sida were
also affected by the storm and had to suspend operations for some
time last night.
</P>
<P>
The meteorological sources predicted that the storm will stop
this night with the fall of rain. 
</P>
</TEXT>
