<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0178 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Vietnamese Farmers Troubled by Rats, Drought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Vietnamese farmers are worried by
the damage caused by rats and drought to their spring crops, Vietnam
News Agency reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
In January and February, nearly 98,000 hectares of paddy fields
were damaged by rats, of which 12,000 hectares were severely or
totally destroyed.
</P>
<P>
Drought is estimated to have caused a loss of 65,000 tons of
coffee beans, or over 1,000 billion Vietnamese dong (77 million
U.S. dollars) in cash term.
</P>
<P>
Of the total 265,000 hectares of summer-autumn rice growing
areas in the central provinces, 90,000 hectares will be affected
by drought, the agency noted.
</P>
<P>
It is forecast that the drought will last through March and
April and the rainfall in the north will decline by between 10-20
percent as compared to the same season of previous years. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
