<HEADLINE> China Records Declining Population Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China's 1997 population growth
rate fell slightly on the previous year.
</P>
<P>
State Statistical Bureau census results for last year show that
the actual birth rate fell by 0.41 permillage points.
</P>
<P>
The birth rate in 1997 stood at 16.57 per thousand, with the
number of births standing at 20.38 million.
</P>
<P>
The fact that China's birth rate has declined steadily over the
past decade indicates that the formerly rapidly rising growth rate
has been effectively controlled.  
