<HEADLINE> Peng Peiyun, Vice-Chairwoman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Peng Peiyun, who was just elected vice-chairwoman of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC):
</P>
<P>
Peng, female; born December, 1929; a native of Liuyang, Hunan
Province; joined Communist Party of China (CPC) May, 1946;
graduated from Qinghua University.
</P>
<P>
Served as secretary of general Party branch in Qinghua
University, 1949-1950; deputy secretary of CPC Beijing University
Committee, 1964-1966.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-minister of Education, 1982-1985; vice-minister
of State Education Commission, 1985-1988; secretary of CPC
Committee of Chinese University of Science and Technology,
1987-1988.
</P>
<P>
Serving as minister in charge of State Family Planning
Commission since 1988; State Councillor since 1993.
</P>
