<HEADLINE> Tomur Dawamat, Vice-Chairman of NPC Standing Committee </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Following is a biographical
sketch of Tomur Dawamat, who was just elected vice-chairman of the
Standing Committee of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC):
</P>
<P>
Tomur Dawamat, male; of Uygur ethnic group; born June, 1927; a
native of Toksun, Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region; joined
Communist Party of China (CPC) December, 1952; started work May,
1950; graduated from Central Institute for Nationalities; college
education.
</P>
<P>
Served as vice-chairman of Xinjiang Autonomous Regional
People's Committee, 1964-1968; secretary of CPC Xinjiang
Autonomous Regional Committee, chairman of Standing Committee of
Autonomous Regional People's Congress, vice-minister of State
Nationalities Affairs Commission, 1979-1985.
</P>
<P>
Served as deputy secretary of CPC Xinjiang Autonomous Regional
Committee, 1985-1996; vice-chairman and chairman of Autonomous
Regional People's Government, 1985-1994.
</P>
<P>
Serving as vice-chairman of NPC Standing Committee since 1993.
</P>
<P>
Member of 12th to 14th CPC Central Committees and member of
Fifth NPC Standing Committee, and vice-chairman of Eighth NPC
Standing Committee. 
</P>
