<HEADLINE> China Retains Lead in Silk Garment Exports to US </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China was the major supplier of
silk garments to the United States in 1997, according to China
International Business Daily published by the Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation.
</P>
<P>
The United States imported silk garments valued at 1.7 billion
US dollars for the fiscal year ending in October
1997, with imports from China accounting for 1.4 billion US
dollars of the total, according to the daily.
</P>
<P>
The daily quoted other reports as saying that the overall value
of China's garment exports to the United States during the first
nine months of 1997 hit 3.7 billion US dollars. China thus joined
Mexico as the two major exporters of garments to the United States.
</P>
<P>
Hong Kong ranked third during the period by exporting textiles
and garments valued at 2.8 billion US dollars to the
U.S. market. 
</P>
