<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0209 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Future of Disputed Bosnian Town Uncertain </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A decision on the future of the
disputed Bosnian town of Brcko has been postponed amid threats
that it could lead to a renewal of the war.
</P>
<P>
The International Arbitration Tribunal decided on Sunday to
postpone the final phase of arbitration until late 1998 or early
1999.
</P>
<P>
The panel said the delay would give Bosnian Serb leaders a
chance to carry out important reforms.
</P>
<P>
The Serbs have administered the town of Brcko since gaining
control at the start of the 1992-95 Bosnian war.
</P>
<P>
Chairman of the tribunal Robert Owen said Brcko would be kept
under international supervision until the final decision is made.
</P>
<P>
A port town of about 40,000 residents on the Sava river, Brcko is
one of the most contentious disputes between postwar Bosnia's ethnic groups.
</P>
<P>
For the Serbs, its six-kilometer corridor is the only passage
linking the western and eastern parts of their territory.
</P>
<P>
But for Croats and Muslims, who formed the majority of Brcko's
population before the war, said that to hand it to the Serbs would
be rewarding "ethnic cleansing".
</P>
<P>
Since neither side could agree on the control of Brcko, the
tribunal was then set up under the 1995 Dayton peace accords.
</P>
<P>
President of the Serbian Republika Srpska Biljana Plavsic
welcomed the tribunal's decision to put off the final
arbitration. She said she would abide by all requirements of the
International Arbitration Tribunal with a view to keeping Brcko in
her republic.
</P>
<P>
Muslim-Croat Federation President Ejup Ganic responded by
saying that if Brcko were given to the Serbs, it would mean the
end of Bosnia and the end of peace for many years.
</P>
<P>
The status of Brcko, the only unsolved dispute under the Dayton
agreement, was to have been decided by December 14, 1996. But due
to the severe differences, the tribunal has already put off the
date of decision for three times. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980316.0210 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
