<HEADLINE> China's New Leadership Elected </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, March 16 (Xinhua) -- China has elected its new
leadership including state president, chairman of the National
People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee and chairman of the
Central Military Commission this morning.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin was re-elected president of the People's Republic
of China (PRC) and chairman of the Central Military Commission, Li
Peng was elected chairman of the NPC Standing Committee and Hu
Jintao was elected vice-president of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
They were elected at the fourth plenary meeting of the First
Session of the Ninth National People's Congress (NPC), China's top
legislature of a new term.
</P>
<P>
At nine o'clock this morning, Li Peng, an executive chairman of
the presidium of the NPC session, announced the opening of today's
plenary meeting. The meeting first approved the scrutineer general
and a list of 33 scrutineers.
</P>
<P>
The election lasted one hour and 50 minutes. At 11:35 A.M., the
results of elections began to be accounced.
</P>
<P>
Li Peng was elected chairman of the Ninth NPC Standing
Committee.
</P>
<P>
The following people were elected vice-chairmen of the Ninth
NPC Standing Committee: Tian Jiyun, Xie Fei, Jiang Chunyun, Zou
Jiahua, Pagbalha Geleg Namgyai, Wang Guangying, Cheng Siyuan,
Buhe, Tomur Dawamat, Wu Jieping, Peng Peiyun, He Luli, Zhou
Guangzhao, Cheng Kejie, Cao Zhi, Ding Shisun, Cheng Siwei, Xu
Jialu and Jiang Zhenghua.
</P>
<P>
He Chunlin was elected secretary-general of the Ninth NPC
Standing Committee.
</P>
<P>
Altogether 134 people were elected members of the Ninth NPC
Standing Committee. The Standing Committee members were elected
through a multi-candidate election method.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin was elected president of the People's Republic of
China and Hu Jintao vice-president of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin was also elected chairman of the Central Military
Commission of the PRC.
</P>
<P>
A total of 2,947 NPC deputies were present at the plenary
meeting today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
