<DATE_TIME> 1998-03-16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Gem Export Earnings Down in 1997 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka exported 219 million
U.S. dollars worth of gem and jewelry in 1997, a drop from a year
earlier, according to media sources here Monday.
</P>
<P>
The Gem and Jewelry Authority (GJA) expects a significant
growth in exports this year following the tax relief provided by
the government for the gold, gem and jewelry industry.
</P>
<P>
These incentives are expected to strengthen the gem industry
further and help Sri Lanka get an edge over other competitors in
the international market, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The best seller among Sri Lanka gems was cut diamonds which
fetched over 131 million U.S. dollars. Other gem exports earned
24.6 million dollars.
</P>
<P>
At present Japan, the United States, Germany, Australia, Italy,
Switzerland, Singapore, Thailand and France are Sri Lanka's major
gem buyers.
</P>
<P>
GJA sources said that there were plans to start a comprehensive
training course in gem heating, treatment, gem cutting and jewelry
designing.
</P>
<P>
There were also plans to establish a school to provide training
in gem and jewelry designing according to international standards.
 
</P>
</TEXT>
