<HEADLINE> International Rhythmic Gymnastics Meet Concludes in Kiev </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KIEV, March 15 (Xinhua) -- The women gymnasts from Ukraine,
Russia and Belarus swept all the medals offered at the three-day
international rhythmic gymnastics meet which concluded here on
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Elena Vitrischenko of Ukraine, world champion and Olympic
bronze medalist, became the triple champion in the individual
all-around, hoop and club events.
</P>
<P>
The four-time champion last year, also reapt two silver medals
in the rope and ribbon competitions.
</P>
<P>
Russian Yanina Batyrschina won the other two events of rope and
ribbon and shared the top honor with Vitrischenko in the club
competition.
</P>
<P>
Batyrschina also added two silvers to her credit in the
all-around and hoop events.
</P>
<P>
Eugenia Pavlina of Belarus won all the bronze medals except the
ribbon competition which was taken away by a Ukrainian entry.
</P>
<P>
The tournament attracted more than 50 women gymnasts from 25
countries, however only two women from Japan and Israel entered
the finals as China failed to send in its athletes. 
</P>
</TEXT>
