<HEADLINE> ECO Ministers Set New Agenda For Cooperation In Transportation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, March 15 (Xinhua) -- A unified system of highways,
railways and civil aviation will be built across the ten states of
the Economic Cooperation organisation by the end of the century.
</P>
<P>
ECO secretary general Onder Ozarn announced the new agenda for
cooperation at the closing of the second meeting of ministers of
transportation and cooperation in Ashkhabad, Turkmenistan, Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ministers also agreed to complete a unified system of
communications among member states.
</P>
<P>
Set up by Pakistan, Iran and Turkey, ECO includes Turkmenistan,
Uzbekistan, Kazakhstan, Azerbaijan, Tajikistan, Kyrgyzstan and
Afganistan.
</P>
<P>
During the first meeting in 1993 of the ECO ministers of
transportation and communications, a general plan for
transportation development was ratified. Since then, 300kms of
railway has been built from Turkmenistan to Iran.
</P>
<P>
A summit of ECO member states is sheduled in May to further
discuss the general development plan. 
</P>
