<HEADLINE> Hainan Improves Telecommunications </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Recent statistics show that the
average number of telephone subscribers in Hainan Province stands
at 8.2:100 people, compared to only 1.3:100 in 1992.
</P>
<P>
The total number of mobile phone subscribers stood at 130,000
at the end of 1997, with 430,000 pager subscribers.
</P>
<P>
Hainan was named as China's newest province in April 1988. The
island province's posts and telecommunications recorded 1997
earning of over 1.6 billion yuan (192.77 million US dollars).
</P>
<P>
Officials noted that the province has attempted to improve
backward telecommunications conditions over the past decade by
injecting substantial funding into building telephone, mobile
phone, paging, and postal facilities. 
</P>
</TEXT>
