<HEADLINE> China's Oldest and Largest Brokerage Vows to Aid Reform </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Shenyin and Wanguo Securities
Co. Ltd., the oldest and largest such company in China, is ready
to enhance its role in the reform of state-owned enterprises, said
Wang Yuchun, company chairman.
</P>
<P>
He said the company will expand its operations in the capital
market by improving its service in regional economic development
projects. It has drawn a scheme for the state-owned enterprises'
industrial capital reform in Shenyang, a city in northeast China's
Liaoning Province, one of China's oldest industrial centers.
</P>
<P>
Wang also stressed the importance of supporting key projects in
Shanghai, Beijing and Shenzhen. The focus will be on bank services
for capital reformation, enterprise purchases and mergers, he said.
</P>
<P>
The brokerage now overlooks all the other domestic securities
firms in business transactions with last year's volume topping
548.3 billion yuan. It also traded 1.6 billion A and B shares last
year.
</P>
<P>
As for this year, Wang said, the company will enlarge its
market share, especially in Hong Kong. It now makes up 1.5 percent
of Hong Kong's security market, raising 1.41 billion Hong Kong
dollars and managing 70 million U.S. dollars of funds for its Hong
Kong clients.
</P>
<P>
The brokerage has 108 sales outlets nationwide generating 870
million yuan in pre-tax profit last year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
