<HEADLINE> Argentina's Gonzales Wins Kenya Golf Open </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Argentina's Ricardo Gonzales
needed a three-hole playoff to beat Kenya's Jacob Okello by one
stroke on Sunday in the Tusker Kenya Open at the 71-par Muthaiga
Golf Club.
</P>
<P>
Prior to the final, Gonzales and Okello was tied in second
place with one shot behind Welshman Mark Litton.
</P>
<P>
Gonzales bogeyed the par-four first hole but recovered withfive
birdies to finish the round at two-under-par 69, while Okello had
six birdies to force a tie with a four-round total of 272.
</P>
<P>
"I felt very bad when I heard that Okello had birdied the 18th
to force the playoff, because I knew I had the game in my hands,"
the 29-year-old Argentine said.
</P>
<P>
The two players were at par on the par-three 13th and par-five
18th. Gonzalez played the third playoff hole at par, but Okello
bogeyed to lose the playoff.
</P>
<P>
Litton and Englishman Bennett Warren tied for third place with
nine-under-par 275 totals.
</P>
<P>
With a history of 31 years, the Kenya Golf Open has attracted
the participation of 45 professionals from 23 countries including
Britain, France, Argentina, Italy, Spain and South Africa. 
</P>
</TEXT>
