<HEADLINE> Italian Police Seeking Art Works Stolen from Albania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, March 16 (Xinhua) -- Italian police in the southern
Adriatic port of Bari are investigating the smuggling of art works
stolen from Albanian museums.
</P>
<P>
The police said fourteenth and fifteenth century masterpieces
had been looted from museums, mostly in the north of Albania, in
the spring of 1997.
</P>
<P>
These works are destined for sale in France and Switzerland
after being transported through Italy, said the Carabinieri, the
Italian national police force.
</P>
<P>
It said the police have asked the Interpol to contact their
Albanian colleagues for more information. 
