<HEADLINE> Slovakia Ice Hockey President Found Shot Dead </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PRAGUE, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Dusan Pasek, president of
Slovakia's Ice Hockey Association, was found shot dead in
Brastislava on Sunday, the official TASR news agency said.
</P>
<P>
Pasek, 37, was found dead from a shot to the head in his office
and a gun was found near his body, the agency said.
</P>
<P>
"Dusan Pasek probably committed suicide. The motive is so far
unknown," TASR quoted Karol Tonka of the Interior Ministry press
department as saying.
</P>
<P>
Born in July, 1960, Pasek was enrolled into the former
Czechoslovakia's national ice hockey team at the age of 18. As a
senior player, he had 196 caps for the national team and won the
world title in 1985.
</P>
<P>
In December 1997, Pasek was elected to the presidency of the
ice hockey association. 
</P>
