<HEADLINE> Vandenbroucke Wins Paris-Nice Cycling Race </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Franck Vandenbroucke of Belgium
clinched the first major title after beating three-time winner
Laurent Jalabert to take the Paris-Nice race on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The 23-year-old Belgian led the race in the overall standings
from the time-trial prologue in Paris and kept it through the rest
of the race.
</P>
<P>
He is the eighth rider in the Paris-Nice history to have worn
the white jersey, which identifies the overall leader, from start
to end.
</P>
<P>
Jalabert was second with 40 seconds behind Vandenbroucke, while
Spain's Marcelino Garcia finished third.
</P>
<P>
The stage win went to Frenchman Christophe Capelle who outpaced
Belgium's Tom Steels in Nice after 161.4 kilometers from Cannes.
