<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, March 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli government is making intense efforts
Sunday to thwart a planned visit by British Foreign Secretary
Robin Cook to the controversial site Har Homa in East Jerusalem.
</P>
<P>
At the weekly Israeli Cabinet session, Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu described as "unacceptable" Cook's planned visit to Har
Homa with Palestinian National Authority (PNA) Minister of
Jerusalem Affairs Faisal Husseini. (Israel-Britain-Cook Visit)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- A strong earthquake on Saturday has killed five
people and injured 50 in Iran's southeastern province of Kerman, a
relief official said on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The official news agency IRNA quoted Red Crescent Society
official Mohammad Dabaghzadeh as saying that the quake inflicted
heavy damage on about 2,000 residential units of 3,600 houses in
the district of Golbaf, some 950 kilometers south of
Tehran. (Iran-Earthquake-Toll)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
TEHRAN -- Iran on Sunday blamed the United States for its
double-standard stance towards nuclear projects in different
countries, and repeated its call for freeing the Middle East from
weapons of mass destruction.
</P>
<P>
According to the official news agency IRNA, Foreign Ministry
spokesman Mahmoud Mohammadi said the U.S. is launching a
"unsubstantiated propaganda" against Iran to divert attention from
the U.S. support for Israel and its stockpile of nuclear
weaponry. (Iran-U.S.-Nuclear Activity)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Arab ministers of justice and interior will sign in
April the first collective Arab anti-terrorism and extremism pact
after four years of debate, the Middle East News Agency reported
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The ministers will convene at the Arab League headquarters in
Cairo on April 22 to endorse the final draft of the deal ahead of
the signing ceremony, said the Egyptian Minister of Justice Farouq
Seif el-Nasr, who unveiled the date of the
signing. (Egypt-Terrorism-Arab Pact)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- An Israeli Air Force brigadier general and his
crewman were killed Sunday morning when their Cobra attack
helicopter crashed into the Mediterranean Sea, Israel TV channel 1
said.
</P>
<P>
Brig. Gen. Tal Shmuel Eldar, 45, and 20-year-old second
lieutenant Ilan Gur, were killed in the chopper crash. Eldar was
the highest-ranking Israel Air Force officer ever killed in an
military air accident. (Israel-Chopper Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- France's leftwing parties led in the regional council
elections by five to nine points ahead of the rightwing, said the
CSA, IPSOS and Sofres polling institutions this evening.
</P>
<P>
The leftwing parties have won 35.4 percent to 38 percent of the
votes, against 29 to 30 percent by the rightwing parties, and 15
percent by the far-right National Front. (France-Regional
Elections-Left Wins) 
