<HEADLINE> Norway's Vik Takes Nordic Combined World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Norway's Olympic gold medalist
Bjarte Engen Vik won the Nordic combined skiing World Cup after
taking a meet in Oslo, Norway, on Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Vik started 26 seconds behind Mario Stecher of Austria in the
cross-country competition but overtook Stecher about halfway
through the 15-kilometer race.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian clocked a time of 40 minutes 58.7 seconds, one
minute 29.6 seconds ahead of Stecher.
</P>
<P>
Vik clinched the Nordic combined World Cup with a total of
1,468 points, ahead of Stecher on 1,440 and Austria's Felix
Gottwald on 854.
</P>
<P>
In a World Cup ski jump event, Primoz Peterka of Slovenia won
his 12th career victory on Sunday, beating Swiss Bruno Reuteler to
second place. 
