<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Clashes Within Anti-Taliban Alliance Intensify in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, March 15 (Xinhua) -- Heavy clashes between two
factions of Afghanistan's anti-Taliban alliance have intensified
in Mazar-e-Sharif, about 300 km north of Kabul, for the second
day, Afghan sources told Xinhua Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Mazar-e-Sharif, headquarters of the northern
alliance, was "highly tense" as forces loyal to ethnic-Uzbek
warlord Rashid Dostum stepped up battle against the Shiite
Hezb-e-Wahdat faction inside the city, said the sources in
Peshawar, a major border city in northwestern Pakistan, Sunday
evening.
</P>
<P>
"Heavy fighting has taken place right inside the center of the
town and the situation can only be described as confusing and
chaotic," the sources said.
</P>
<P>
However, no further details on the clashes or information on
casualties were immediately available, they said.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistan-based private Afghan Islamic Press reported
Saturday that dozens of people had been killed in the clashes.
</P>
<P>
Mazar-e-Sharif, de facto capital of the northern alliance, is
the only largest city outside the control of the Islamic Taliban
militia.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Dostum's forces have launched an all-out offensive
on Heritan, a strategic town bordering Uzbekistan, in a bid to
take it back from the hands of the Hezb-e-Wahdat faction, the
Afghan sources said.
</P>
<P>
Dostum had lost control of Heritan since mid-1997 when his
right-hand man general Abdul Malik revolted against him in
Mazar-e-Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The northern alliance, composed of forces led by Dostum,
Hezb-e-Wadhat and former Afghanistan's military chief Ahmad
Masood, has been battling the hardline Taliban, who control two
thirds of Afghanistan, since Taliban drove them out from the
capital city of Kabul in September 1996.
</P>
<P>
The Shiite Hezb-e-Wahdat rose to dominate the historic
Mazar-e-Sharif late last year when it led a massive defense of the
city from a major Taliban assault in September.
</P>
<P>
Since then Dostum, who once formed the dominant power in the
city, has been attempting to regain control of the dusty
stronghold. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
